100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 1, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, pushing forward discussions on disarmament amid rising tensions in Europe. In the United States, a major winter storm brought heavy snowfall across the Midwest, disrupting travel and causing power outages. Meanwhile, the trial of the "Scopes Monkey Case" continued to attract national attention, highlighting the clash between science and religion in American society.
